commit.message: iOS: Fix issue #84 (crash caused by un-implemented delegate method -overlayDidAppear)
Android: Correctly reflect MRAID capabilities in ad request
iOS: Fix bug preventing loading indicator from being dismissed properly for HTML interstitials; fix bug which allows the browser controller to continue loading after it has been dismissed

Merge remote-tracking branch 'upstream/master' into mopub-merge

Conflicts:
	Android/mopub-android-sdk/src/com/mopub/mobileads/AdView.java
Android: Handle inability to retrieve fbattrid more robustly
Android: Add testing accessors to MoPubView and MoPubInterstitial
iOS: Add 'testing' property on MPAdView and MPInterstitialAdController
iOS: Increase accuracy of iAd impression tracking
Android: Perform HttpClient shutdown on background thread
Release: version 1.9
iOS: Add support for ASIdentifierManager (UIDevice.identifierForAdvertising replacement)
Fixed the opening of a browser using url. Fix was already in the latest release of mopub on github.
iOS: Enable UDID conditional compilation
iOS: Re-introduce UDID but with a preprocessor directive to control its compilation; remove persistence of device identifier; fix compiler error relating to CALayer
Release: version 1.8
Added support of local path for ads in moPub library
merge
Release: version 1.7
Updates for orientation fixes and full-frame takeover size.
iOS: Improve click experience to avoid blank browser screen when loading a URL with many redirects; fix issue with browser not dismissing when using -[UIApplication openURL:]
iOS: Fix an issue in which the MRAID.isViewable API would return an inaccurate value; resolve issue #59 (MPAdView no longer implicitly alters its .hidden property)
Set the sayMedia flag for our SDK.
Release: version 1.6
Android: Fix loading of mraid.js from disk on Android 4.0+

iOS: Add support for displaying an interstitial from an arbitrary view controller via -showFromViewController; add interstitial delegate property and deprecate parent property; modify MPInterstitialAdControllerDelegate so that it no longer inherits from MPAdViewDelegate
Support traditional linking, with assets in root of application.
Use bounds of screen to avoid gap for status bar which is always hidden for takeovers.
Fixes to hide status bar for takeover.
Android: Use ThreadPoolExecutor for AsyncTasks on Android 4.0+; refactor URL loading logic into AdFetcher
Hide status bar (if visible) for ad takeover.
